-- Japanese Bought Net 391.3 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-01-17T23:52:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-17/japanese-bought-net-391-3-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Jan. 11 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 391.3 billion yen ($4.4 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 155.3 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 55.8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 180.1 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 139 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 233.8 billion yen in stocks, and bought 2806.9 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 3179.7
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
